        "content": "<p>Is there a way to given a structure's constructor a different name than <code>mk</code>? (Aside from declaring it with <code>inductive</code> and losing all the structure niceties)</p>",
        "id": 261994247,
        "sender_full_name": "Marcus Rossel",
        "timestamp": 1637271281
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes <a href=\"https://leanprover.github.io/lean4/doc/struct.html\">https://leanprover.github.io/lean4/doc/struct.html</a> <a href=\"https://leanprover.github.io/lean4/doc/declarations.html#structures-and-records\">https://leanprover.github.io/lean4/doc/declarations.html#structures-and-records</a></p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">structure</span> <span class=\"n\">Point</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">α</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span> <span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"n\">where</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">create</span> <span class=\"o\">::</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">α</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">y</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">α</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 261998095,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1637273129
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">structure</span> <span class=\"n\">A</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"n\">myCtor</span> <span class=\"o\">::</span>\n<span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">field1</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">field2</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">Char</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 261998099,
